A 1915 biographical sketch:
&quot;&quot;Emma Roberts was born in Henderson, KY. She received her education at Randolph College in that city, completing her four-year course in three years. She afterward moved to New York, and there devoted herself entirely to the study of singing, working with Miss Callender. After having been soloist with the New York Symphony Orchestra in 1912, she went to Europe, where she studied for two years, coaching her operatic roles in Paris, Berlin and Munich. She was engaged to sing in opera in several of the important cities of Europe in the season of 1914-1915, but returned to America on account of the war. Since her return she has been heard with the important symphony orchestras and in recital in many of the large cities of the country.&quot;
