&quot;The Edison Company has fashioned a remarkably lifelike representation of a Belgian village somewhere near Mineola NY.  Stucco concrete and other materials have been used;heavy wooden signs swinging from iron supports and marked with Belgian captions indicate hotels and public places; there is a cobbled street where the fighting takes place and the whole conveys an impression of 16th Century architecture that would be very hard to find elsewhere in the United States.  They have also built a dug out in their Bronx NY studio that is the last word in realism. [...] As yet there is no sub title to The Three Things the interpretation is probably Liberty Fraternity and Democracy The picture is expected to be finished about the end of November 
