We're still working on a method to capture the data, but we recently located boxes of Harris &amp; Ewing catalog cards which have captions for some of the untitled photos. I looked this one up, as well as the photo before it, <a href="https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2016880217/" rel="noreferrer nofollow">www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2016880217/</a>, which shows the same two ladies. Harris and Ewing used the same caption for both photos, but it fits with the first one better as it has the man on the right. The caption says: 

&quot;WINS MIDDLE ATLANTIC GOLF TITLE FOR WOMEN.  This photograph shows the awarding of the prize to the new Middle Atlantic golf champion, Mrs. David H. Clark, Army &amp; Navy Club of Washington. From the left Mrs. Clark, Miss Lily Harper, 19-year-old Portsmouth, Va., runner-up, and Charles H. Doing, Jr., president of the Washington Golf  &amp; Country Club, awarding the prize. The matches were held on the Washington course. 10-12-34&quot;

Just to confirm that, I looked through some newspapers at the time. I didn't find a published version of either photo, but the Washington Post of 10-12-1934 (page 19) published photos of both ladies playing golf, so I can confirm it is them. We'll update the catalog records with the captions.
